{"word":"γεραίρω","slug":"γεραίρω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γεραίρω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γέρας'><el>γέρας</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to honour</i> or <i>reward with</i> a gift, <el>τινά τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be so honoured</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>reversely, <el>γ. τινί τι</el> <i>to present as an honorary gift</i>, <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to celebrate</i>, <el>χοροῖσι</el> <i>with</i> dances, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}